@node Startup "Getting started"

IconAuthor can be called from the CLI by typing:

            [prompt]> IconAuthor [iff-file|icon-file] <return>

On  WorkBench  it  behaves  completely  normal:  just doubleclick its icon.
(nice one, isn't it ?) U may shift-select the first project to work with.

If  U did "Save Settings" in the menue @{" Settings " link Settings } the last project (icon or
iff-image)  will  be loaded first.  If it starts with an iff-picture U will
first see the @{" ImageScreen." link ImageScreen }

Normally U will first see IconAuthor's @{" Window." link Window }

There's always an online-help available, if @"Hyper" has been installed correctly.
If running from a disk, it may need two timmes pressing `help' to start hyper
the first time.

@endnode

@node Window "The IconAuthor window"

The window will appear on the WorkBenchScreen.  (size is 640x200).

On the left side  you see the @{" ShowField " link ShowField } where the images  are shown.  The
maximum  size  is 256x128 pixels.  It is adjustable using the sliders below
and  at  the right side of the field, so called x- and y-slider.  Width and
height are indicated by borderlines and numerical displays.  Play it.

In some part of the window you find the @{" Gadgets." link Gadgets }

And of course there are some @{" Menues " link Menues} attached.

@endnode

@node Gadgets "IconAuthor v1.05 - the gadgets"

