                             @{" " link exy }
 @{"          X Slider          " link exy}     @{"      OKAY     " link OKAY    }     @{"     Magnify    " link Magnify }

@endnode

@node Color "Editor -- Color"

4 colours and 4 halftones used for the draw functions:

    @{"Free" link Free}, @{"Lines" link Line}, @{"Rects" link Rect}, @{"Fill" link Fill}, @{"Negativ" link Neg}

@{"Texts" link Text} and @{"Circles" link Circ} can only use the 4 basic colours.

@endnode

@node Templates "Editor -- Templates"

12 line-templates used for the draw functions:

    @{"Free" link Free}, @{"Lines" link Line}, @{"Rects" link Rect}, @{"Fill" link Fill}, @{"Negativ" link Neg}

@{"Texts" link Text} and @{"Circles" link Circ} can only use the 4 basic colours.

@endnode

@node Pensize "Editor -- Pensize"

Choose the size of the pen used to draw free, lines or rectangles.

@{"Texts" link Text} and @{"Circles" link Circ} do ignore that.

Bigger brushes are fine with templates and halftones.

@endnode

@node Flip "Editor -- Flip X/Y"

(shortcuts "X", "Y")

Flip the image (or the aktive {"brush" link Brush}) on its x- or y-axis.

@endnode

@node Neg "Editor -- Negativ"

Fill  the  whole  imagearea  (or the aktive {"brush" link Brush}) using  the Complement-mode.
Choosing halftone @{"colours" link Color} or @{"templates" link Templates } will result in some interesting
processes (not for the brush, sorry).

@endnode

@node Free "Editor/DrawTools -- Free"

(shortcut "e")

Draw  free  lines or just points using the color chosen from the palette by
pressing the left mousebutton and moving.
Release  the  left  mousebutton to use the chosen color/template or release
and click the right one to get a result in "COMPLEMENT" mode.

@endnode

@node Line "Editor/DrawTools -- Line"

(shortcut "L")

Draw straight lines by positioning the pointer on the starting point, press
the  left  mousebutton  and  move  the  mouse  to  the end of the new line.
Release  the  left  mousebutton to use the chosen color/template or release
and click the right one to get a result in "COMPLEMENT" mode.

@endnode

@node Rect "Editor/DrawTools -- Rect"

(shortcut "R")

Draw rectangles by  positioning the crosshair on the starting corner, press
the  left  mousebutton  and move the mouse to the opposite corner.  Release
the  left mousebutton to use the chosen color/template or release and click
the right one to get a result in "COMPLEMENT" mode.

@endnode

@node Circ "Editor/DrawTools -- Circle"

(shortcut "C")

Draw  circles by positioning the crosshair on the centerpoint, press the left
mousebutton  and  move the mouse to the left or right to adjust the radius.
Release  the  left  mousebutton to use the color chosen from the palette or
release and click the right one to get a result in "COMPLEMENT" mode.

Pens greater than one pixel and templates are ignored.

@endnode

@node Fill "Editor/DrawTools -- Fill"

(shortcut "F")

Fill  closed  areas using the chosen color/template
by pressing the left mousebutton.

@endnode

@node Text "Editor/DrawTools -- Text"

                               (shortcut "T")

When  first used, this gadget opens the @{"fontrequester" link SetFont}.  The chosen font
will   be   used  to  render  your  string.   Different  styles  (bold,
italic,...) are supported.  Edit the text in the @{"string gadget" link String} below.

Place  it by moving the pointer in the showfield while keeping the left
mousebutton  pressed.   Release  the  left mousebutton to use the color
chosen  from  the  palette  or release and click the right one to get a
result in "COMPLEMENT" mode.

@endnode

@node Brush "Editor/DrawTools -- Brush"

(shortcut "B")

Cut out a rectangle from inside the showfield by positioning  the crosshair
on the  starting  corner,  press the left mousebutton and move the mouse to
the opposite  corner.  Place it by moving  the pointer in the showfield and
place it with a click of the left mousebutton.

The funktions @{"Flip x/y" link Flip} and @{"Negativ" link Neg} modify the brush.
The shortcut "B" starts the cut-mode quickly.
By swapping the images with "J" U may carry the brush to the other image.

@endnode

@node SetFont "Editor/DrawTools/Text -- SetFont"

(shortcut "F")

Only  active  in  "Text"  mode.   This gadget opens the fontrequester.  The
chosen  font  will  be  used  to  render  your  string.   Different  styles
(bold, italic, ...) and colours are supported.

@endnode

@node String "Editor/DrawTools/Text -- String gadget"

Enter your text here (64 chars max)

@endnode

@node Magnify "Editor -- Magnify"

Slider to choose the magnification-factor.
The @{"x/y-sliders" link exy} reflect and move the magnified area.

@endnode

@node exy "Editor -- x/y-sliders"

They  will reflect and move the @{"magnified" link Magnify} area.
Movement can be controlled by the cursor-keys also.

@endnode

@node OKAY "Editor -- OKAY"

(shortcut "O")

Keep it like it is and return from editing mode.

@endnode

@node SaveIFF "Gadgets -- Save IFF Brush"

(shortcut "B")

The  image  shown  in the left field of the window will be saved in the IFF
brush  format,  so  you  can  edit it with dpa*nt or whatever you like.  An
ASL-filerequester  will  pop  up.  The suffix '.iff' is used as the default
search  pattern  and  attached  to  the  actual  projectname  to  build the
suggested  savename.   The  used  path  will  be  kept  in memory for later
save-brush-calls.

NOTE:

You  may  reload  that  brush (using the clipboard...) into IconAuthor.  To
get the  correct result,  adjust  contrast  and  brightness  to  zero.  Now
playing with these values results  in  new  color  combinations.   Changing
the  size  will  produce different rasters.

@endnode

@node SaveIcon "Gadgets -- Save Icon File"

(shortcut "S")
The  image  shown in the left field of the window will be saved as an icon.
When saving an Icon the window will look like this:"
  __________________________
 |                          |    @{" ToolTypes " link ToolTypes  }        @{" Icon Style " link IconStyle }
 |                          |     _________         o Complement
 |                          |    |         |        o Highlight
 |     here is the icon     |    |         |        o Backfill
 |                          |    |         |        @{" Icon Type  " link IconType    }
 |                          |    |_________|        o Disk
 |                          |                       o Drawer
 |                          |    @{" StackSize " link StackSize  }        o Tool
 |                          |    @{"DefaultTool" link DefaultTool}        o Project
 |                          |                       o Garbage
 |__________________________|    @{"Drawer Data" link DrawerData }        @{"Save" link Save } @{"Go Back" link GoBack   }

 NOTE:      The right mousebutton simulates a selection of the icon!
            The shortcut "J" swaps the images!

@endnode

@node ToolTypes "Save As Icon -- ToolTypes"

Tool- and Project-icons may give parameters to the program they call.
These are stored as an array of strings in the .info file. If an icon
U load or want to overwrite contains such tooltypes, U are asked to use
these old ones or those U edit here. Type a new tooltype in the string-
gadget and press <return> to add it to the list. To remove one from the
list, choose it with a mouseclick and then clear the stringgadget with
<ctrl-x>; <return> will finally remove it.

NOTE: The strings may be much longer than shown in the listfield.
      Select them into the stringgadget and move the cursor to the
      right to read them completely.

@endnode

@node DrawerData "Save As Icon -- Edit DrawerData"

  Disk-, Drawer- and Garbage-icons open a window when U doubleclick them.
  The position and size of this window is stored in a NewWindow-struct
  in the .info file. Enter Ur preferred integers here.

@endnode

@node IconType "Save As Icon -- Icon Type"

Select one of the following:

    DISK
    DRAWER
    TOOL
    PROJECT
    GARBAGE

@endnode

@node IconStyle "Save As Icon -- Icon Style"

Select one of the following:

    COMPLEMENT
    HIGH IMAGE
    BACKFILLED

@endnode

@node DefaultTool "Save As Icon -- Default Tool"

  Enter the path to your tool for Disk & Project icons here.

@endnode

@node StackSize "Save As Icon -- Stack"

   1024   /*  be      */
   2048   /*  careful */
   4096
   9182
  18364
  32768

The stacksize of loaded icons are rounded up!

@endnode

@node GoBack "Save As Icon -- Go Back"

(shortcut "B")

Ready, back to the first @{"window" link Window}.

@endnode

@node Save "Save As Icon -- Save"

(shortcut "S")

An  ASL-filerequester  will  pop  up.   The  suffix  '.info' is used as the
default  search pattern and attached to the actual projectname to build the
suggested  savename.   The  used  path  will  be  kept  in memory for later
save-icon-calls.

If an icon
U want to overwrite contains @{"tooltypes" link ToolTypes}, U are asked to use these old ones or
those U edited.

@endnode

@node SaveData "Gadgets -- Save Image Data"

(shortcut "I")

The  image  shown  in  the  left  field  of  the window will be saved as an
ASCII-file  containing  imagedata  in  a  form usable to include it in your
C-programcode.   It also contains a small "main()" function to check things
immediately.   An  ASL- filerequester will pop up.  The suffix '.c' is used
as   the   default   search   pattern   and   attached  to  the  associated
picturefilename as the suggested name to save it as.  The used path will be
kept in memory for later save-data-calls.

NOTE: This gadget is not rendered, if U didn't save SRC in the @{"settings" link SaveSettings}

@endnode

@node QUIT "Gadgets -- Q U I T"

@{"Thanxs" link Credits} for using it.

@endnode

@node xy "Gadgets -- x/y slider"

Use these to control size parameters - to resize if the image is not locked,
or to define the borderlines if image is @{" locked." link Lock }

The  size  you  adjust  using  the  sliders  (or  the cursor- keys) will be
rerendered  as soon as you release the slider.  After changing the image in
Edit-Picture-mode  the  size  of  the  image  to  save is selected by these
sliders.   Only symetric sizing is possible here - define unreachable parts
on  the  @{" ImageScreen." link ImageScreen }    The selected part of the picture does not include
the borderlines, it's exactly between them.

Use cursor keys to shortcut.

@endnode

@node Menues "The Menues"

The  menues  are exactly the same as in Commodores IconEdit2.0.  But U will
soon  notice  some enhanced functions, corresponding with those U can reach
by the gadgets.

So only the differences are described here.

                        @{" Images " link Images }
                        @{" Extras " link Extras }

                        @{"Settings/Use grid     " link UseGrid}
                        @{"Settings/Save Settings" link SaveSettings}

@endnode

@node Images "Menues -- Images/Use Template"

 U  can  choose  one  of 12 templates, that will fill the marked area in the
 showfield.  A 3D-border will be added.

@endnode

@node Extras "Menues -- Extras/AutoTopleft"

This will center the image in its smallest boundaries.

@endnode

@node UseGrid "Menues -- Settings/Use Grid?"

No function yet

@endnode

@node SaveSettings "Menues -- Settings/Save Settings"

 The preferences are saved as tooltypes of the IconAuthor.info iconfile.  If
 no Icon exists, a new one is created when Save is selected.
 A new window will pop up, letting U edit all preferences comfortly.
 The  paths may be selected using the asl-requester  by selecting the button
 at the left side of the string-gadgets.
                     _               _________
        @{"   clipunit " link Clip    }[_] @{" palette    " link Commands }[_________] @{"    noicons " link Flags }
        @{"       xmag " link xymag   }[_] @{" showclip   " link Commands }[_________] @{"     nogrid " link Flags }
        @{"       ymag " link xymag   }[_] @{" hypertext  " link Commands }[_________] @{"        src " link Flags }
        @{"   leftedge " link Windows }[_] @{" icondrawer " link Paths    }[_________]
        @{"    topedge " link Windows }[_] @{" ilbmdrawer " link Paths    }[_________] @{"  Default   " link Setgads }
        @{" frleftedge " link Windows }[_] @{" srcdrawer  " link Paths    }[_________] @{" Last Saved " link Setgads }
        @{"  frtopedge " link Windows }[_] @{" clipdrawer " link Paths    }[_________] @{"    Save    " link Setgads }
        @{"    frwidth " link Windows }[_] @{" altdrawer  " link Paths    }[_________] @{"    Use     " link Setgads }
        @{"   frheight " link Windows }[_] @{" projname   " link Paths    }[_________] @{"   Cancel   " link Setgads }

@endnode

@node SetGads "Settings -- Gadgets"

There are also some whatUthinkiswhatUget-gadgets:

         Default     (shortcut "D")
         Last Saved  (shortcut "L")
         Save        (shortcut "S")
         Use         (shortcut "U")
         Cancel      (shortcut "C")

@endnode

@node Clip "Settings -- Clip Unit"

# of clip used by the clipboard functions

@endnode

@node xymag "Settings -- Xmag/Ymag"

# no function yet

@endnode

@node Windows "Settings -- Window Positioning"

Left/Topedge          # place the mainwindow
                        default: 0/0

FrLeftEdge/FrTopedge  # place the aslrequester
                        default: 4/11

FrWidth/FrHeight      # size the aslrequester
                        default: 310/187

@endnode

@node Commands "Settings -- External Commands"

Palette   --  path to command to use palette-requester
              default: "SYS:Utilities/Palette"

ShowClip  --  path to command to display clipboard-brush
              default: intern

HyperText --  path to command to display help texts
              that will be called for first aid:
              default: "SYS:Utilities/Hyper S"

@endnode

@node Paths "Settings -- Default Paths"

IconDrawer  --  default path to load icons
                default: ENVARC:sys/

IlbmDrawer  --  default path to save iff-brushes
                default: Ram:

SrcDrawer   --  default path to save c-data-files
                default: Ram:

ClipDrawer  --  default path to load iff-pictures
                default: Ram:

AltDrawer   --  default path to save icons
                default: Ram:

Projname    --  path to the default image to load,
                don't add ".info" for icons,
                iff-pictures are possible here too
                default: ENVARC:sys/def_tool

@endnode

@node Flags "Settings -- Flags"

NoIcons  --  they  will  not be added to c-code
             or iff-brushes when saveing them
             default: add Icons

NoGrid   --  no function yet
             default: off

Src      --  enable source-creation
             default: on

@endnode

@node Lock "Gadgets -- Lock"

(shortcut "k")

The  shown  image  may  be  in  two  very  different  states controlled and
displayed  by the "Lock" gadget above the image.  If the state is "Locked",
U  can't  use  the  sliders  to  process the image.  Instead there are some
statistics  shown about the actual project and the @{"x/y-sliders" link xy } will control
the edges of the image used for savings and if U swap to the other image.

If the state of the image is not "Locked", U may process the image.  If the
original  cut  of an iff- picture is still in memory, this is the source of
the  process,  else the image is copied to the clipboard and U can choose a
cut of it on the @{" ImageScreen." link  ImageScreen }

@endnode

@node ImageScreen "The ImageScreen"

When you selected a picture to load,
it will be shown centered on a new
screen, which modes are set accor-
ding to the pictures viewmodes.

Now  wait  a  second.  Clicking the
right mousebutton or pressing
"return", "esc"  or "enter" brings
U back to the WorkBench immediately.
But moving with the left mousebutton
pressed you can define a rectangular
area that will be used for the image
processing.
To choose a new rectangle, switch
the left button again.
The right button brings the cutted
area back, centered on the Image-
Screen and again  you may define it
more exactly if necessary
...  and so on  ...
until you finnally go back to the
WorkBench. If you don't cut anything
the original size of the loaded
picture/brush will be base of
resizing.

When you're returned to the
IconAuthor window, you'll find
the size-sliders and the
associated borderlines in the
showfield changed to present
the pictures  x:y  aspects.
If the picture/cutout is bigger
than 256x128, the maximum size
possible is adjusted; if it
fits, the original size is set.

@endnode

