@node Contents "Distribution"

IconAuthorDemo    Done to replace IconEdit2.0. It can transform IFF
                  images  or brushes into resized 2-BitPlane brushes
                  or iconfiles that match the WorkBench2.0 colors.
                  Hypertext-Online-Help is available via `Hyper'.
                  The program is shareware and this demo is limited
                  to process the provided demo image only.
                  Needs OS2.xx. Version 1.06, update to Disk #739,
                  Author: Koessi.

IconAuthor.hyper  Documentation of IconAuthorDemo v1.06. Should be
                  placed in the assigned device "HYPER:" for perma-
                  nent access. Author: Koessi.

Demo.pic          A very nice Hires-B&W-picture as found on Amiga-
                  LibDisk #58 - thanx Fred.

Install           A script to copy IconAuthor to Ur SYS:-device in
                  a useable form, installing Hyper also.

Hello             A script assigning "HYPER:" to :Hyper/ and adding
                  the fonts to Ur fonts:-list. This will leave some
                  locks on this disk, but is okay for a first test.

MySysInfo         The system-configuration, I use for programming
                  and with which IconAuthor runs problemless.
                  Please notify differences when reporting bugs to
                  me, thanx.

This Demo may be copied and spreaded as long as all files are kept
untouched with it and the price for the disk containing it is not
higher than DM/$ 5,00. If U paid more, U're fooled and DON'T BUY
ANYMORE FROM THAT RAT.

@endnode

@node Help "Interactive Helpsytem"


In the @{"`Save Settings'" link SaveSettings} menu or in the
tooltypes U can define

HYPERTEXT --  path to command to display help texts
              will be called like this:
              "@{"hyper" link hyper.hyper/MAIN} iconauthor.hyper/gadgets"
              when pressing the "Help" key

The shown chapter describes the IconAuthor's actual state.

There are several shortcuts build in to access functions via
keyboard:

Return       - <q>, <Enter>, <Esc>, <Return>
Load Doc     - <l>, <Ins>
First Page   - <f>, <Home>
Prev Page    - <p>, <PgUp>,  <Backspace>, <Right mousebutton>
Next Page    - <n>, <PgDn>,  <Space>,
Sleep        - <s>, <Enter>
Gads on/off  - <Shift-g>
Help         - <h>, <Help>   (try to load this text)

Scroll-up    - <cursor-up>,    <kp8>
Scroll-down  - <cursor-down>,  <kp2>
Scroll-left  - <cursor-left>,  <kp4>
Scroll-right - <cursor-right>, <kp6>

@endnode

@node History "History"

1.00   9.92   first release on Fish 739
1.01  10.92   second release on APC&TCP 37 & KickStart 545
              several optimizings done
1.02  10.92   first registrated version
              new: supports/needs Hyper >= v1.10
              bugs in editmode removed
              (switching between images caused shift downwards)
              several optimizings done
1.03  10.92   bug in saveiconmode removed
              (didn't add ".info" automatically)
1.04  10.92   new: crosshair in editmode/rect&brush
                   idea came from Lothar, thanx
                   switch off the pointer if possible (line etc...)
                   now ignores keyboard in some paintmodes
              bug in memorymanagement removed (lost chipmem)
              bug reported that program failes in editmode
              on A2000 without ECS, anyone else found that ?
1.05  11.92   bug in its own icon structure detected
              new: crosshair in editmode/circle positioning
                   shortcuts for tools-mx-gads in editmode
                   tooltypes & drawerdata editable in savemode
1.05a 11.92   second registrated version
              new: crosshair on imagescreen to ease cutting
                   progressindicator for colorprocess of >4plane-images
                   smarter behavior on more-than-4-colors-workbench
                   (still no! 8/16-color-support, maybe in v2.0)
                   german documentation
1.05b 11.92   Error in save-deftool removed (another requester)
              Error in Editor/Textmode removed
              new: supports/needs Hyper >= v1.14
                   calculates SA_Pens for ImageScreen
1.05c 11.92   new: supports/needs Hyper >= v1.15
                   sends windowposition to Hyper
                   Brush-handling improved:
                      flip-x/y and negativ now change the active brush
                      no mousepointer when placing the brush (now with
                      a click of the left mousebutton)
1.05d 11.92   Error (new) in brushmode removed (magnifyer)
              Error in programmicon removed (now loadable)
1.06  11.92   Error im Editmode removed (templategadget now ok disabled)
              magnifyer-behavior in brushmode improved
              Negativ-Gadget is a button now (shortcut 'N')
              shortcuts in editor now only locked when adjusting something
                      (crosshair, line, rects or text)
              Error in Stack-load/save-routine removed, ...
              Load-which-image-requester changed (First|Both|Second)
                      (merci Frķdķric)

known bugs:
            * switch in preferences-editor (NOICONS, NOGRID, SRC)
              not always in correct state
            * problems on 1MB-chip machines ??? (removed ReportMouse())

@endnode

